es.<br>
<br>
Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wolfofwynter>Wolf of Wynter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/4/03 8:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Velious faction</span><hr size=1> By the way, I did read the post at the top of the forum first. I guess I'm just fishing for war stories from warriors that have worked the various factions in Velious and what rewards in equipment I should look for. Espically if there are items on differant factions I might want to strive for. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hussarian>hussarian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/4/03 10:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Velious faction</span><hr size=1> There's 3 main factions: Dwarves, Giants, Dragons<br>
Dwarves: start indiff, source of the coldain rings (9th and 10th have nice stats), and source of the shawls (very nice for casters).  The armor quested from them is the lowest of the 3 factions, but is also the easiest to get.  The drops come from Kael (giant city).  Though it's the lowest of the armors, it's still usually very good for people low 50's and even into the 60's if they don't have a guild that can do Temple of Veeshan.  Dwarves hate the giants, and don't care at all about the dragons.  Nothing done to dwarves will effect dragon factions, nothing done to dragons will effect dwarf factions.<br>
<br>
Giants: unless you worship rallos zek, you start kos.  There are 3 giant factions - Kromrif (hate the dwarves most of all), Kromzek (hate the dragons most of all), and King Tormax.  The armor quested from the giants comes from the Zek giants, and the main drops come from Temple of Veeshan, west wing.  The armor has the highest ac of all velious factions.<br>
<br>
Dragons: everyone starts kos.  Unless you get a faction hit from Vindi, Statue, or AoW, you will have to spend a long while in Kael killing giants to get non kos.  The armor quested from them have the best stats of the velious factions.  The main drops for the armor come from Halls of Testing in Temple of Veeshan (east wing).<br>
<br>
My suggestion, kill giants, get the drops to turn in to Thurgadin (dwarf city).  The coldain rings are very nice, the 8th gives an instant click 8 point damage shield, the 9th has good stats and the same effect, the 10th requires a fairly bigger guild to complete, but gives very nice stats.  After you've worked on Thurg armor and rings (and shawls for casters), then it's the time to pick giants or dragons.  By the time that happens, and you need to choose between the two, you will most likely know which one fits you better. <p>Veteran Overdorf <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18306">Hussar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Kneeslicer - Drunken Tsunami</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dobbobaggins>Dobbo Baggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/03 10:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Velious faction questions</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>you will have to spend a long while in Kael killing giants to get non kos<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> that is a big understatement. today half a ring war 4 arena raids 3 sk guilds. warmly or kindly can't remember. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=1ludor>1Ludor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/10/03 12:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Velious faction questions</span><hr size=1> many dragons in WW are one group doable, above the ntov scar off to the left along the coastline is the best camp spot. easy farming for frostbringers and dragon armor. most dispel one buff at a time and someone needs to watch for roamers.<br>
<br>
farming armor items depends alot on your diety and pp, all the armor out of ntov is inferior to diety class armor. most ppl will want to farm dragon armor since its better for all classes EXCEPT warriors = ( , if u got diety armor u wont care either way. you will need to fix faction with dragons by killing mobs in kael, higher lvl mobs give more faction. easier to get to and kill for east tov(dragon) armor too, plus 1-2 groups killing dozekar now for some of the best items in the game.<br>
<br>
the ONLY reason to be on giant faction is for the tormax's quests of killing the dorf and dragon kings, both require 25-35 ppl to kill at least. u could do warrior quest armor too, but i doubt that will happen. vindicator, statue, and tormax are 3-5 group kills anyways for easy good loot.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=577575&amp;resize=true" target="top">Ludor Sheolbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
